pageTitle: Levy officers get their man a year later | ChieflandCitizen.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {34700=Copyright © 2015, 20717=A drug bust in Chiefland last year has led to the arrest of a Melrose man who initially escaped arrest by the Levy County Sheriff's Office, but has found out he could not escape their notice, according to a Sheriff's Office press release. Kenyatta Daron Howard, 36, of Melrose, was arrested Saturday, March 30, for possession of a controlled substance with intent to sell or deliver and possession of drug paraphernalia by Sheriff's Capt.
